│ The crash was caused by using stale `Value*` pointers as     │
│ keys for a `DenseMap` lookup. These pointers referred to     │
│ instructions that had already been vectorized and replaced,  │
│ and thus were no longer present in the map. The fix involves │
│ two small changes:                                           │
│ 1.  Populating `SameValuesCounter` with the current, tracked │
│ values instead of the original, possibly stale, values.      │
│ 2.  Adjusting the subsequent `transform` call to use these   │
│ tracked values directly, removing the incorrect and          │
│ unnecessary lookup in `TrackedVals`.                         │
│                                                              │
│ These changes ensure that the vectorizer correctly handles   │
│ cases where the operands of a reduction are themselves part  │
│ of the set of values being vectorized, preventing the crash. │
