│ This is an interesting bug in the SLP vectorizer's           │
│ horizontal reduction logic. The crash is due to using stale  │
│ `Value*` pointers as keys for a `DenseMap` lookup after they │
│ have been vectorized and replaced within the same reduction  │
│ analysis step.                                               │
│                                                              │
│ Here is my plan to fix it:                                   │
│                                                              │
│ 1.  **Analyze the Root Cause**: The root cause analysis      │
│ correctly identifies that `SameValuesCounter` is populated   │
│ with original `Value*`s. When a sub-part of the reduction is │
│ vectorized, these original values might be replaced. The     │
│ `TrackedVals` map is updated to reflect this, but            │
│ `SameValuesCounter` is not, leading to a failed lookup when  │
│ trying to reconstruct the `Candidates` list.                 │
│                                                              │
│ 2.  **Propose a Fix**: The fix involves two coordinated      │
│ changes:                                                     │
│     *   First, I will modify the population of               │
│ `SameValuesCounter` to use the currently tracked values as   │
│ keys, instead of the original, potentially stale, values.    │
│ This ensures the keys in `SameValuesCounter` remain          │
│ consistent with the values being tracked in `TrackedVals`.   │
│     *   Second, because `SameValuesCounter` now holds the    │
│ correct, up-to-date values, the subsequent `transform`       │
│ operation that rebuilds the `Candidates` list no longer      │
│ needs to perform a lookup in `TrackedVals`. It can use the   │
│ keys from `SameValuesCounter` directly.                      │
│                                                              │
│ 3.  **Implement the Fix**: I will now apply these changes    │
│ using the `edit` tool.                                       │
│                                                              │
│ <tool_call>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "edit",                                            │
│   "args": {                                                  │
│     "file":                                                  │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp",           │
│     "old": "          Value *OrigV = TrackedToOrig.at(V);\n  │
│ ++SameValuesCounter.try_emplace(OrigV).first->second;",      │
│     "new": "                                                 │
│ ++SameValuesCounter.try_emplace(V).first->second;"           │
│   }                                                          │
│ }                                                            │
│ </tool_call>                                                 │
│ <tool_call>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "edit",                                            │
│   "args": {                                                  │
│     "file":                                                  │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp",           │
│     "old": "        transform(SameValuesCounter,             │
│ Candidates.begin(),\n                  [&](const auto &P) {  │
│ return TrackedVals.at(P.first); });",                        │
│     "new": "        transform(SameValuesCounter,             │
│ Candidates.begin(),\n                  [](const auto &P) {   │
│ return P.first; });"                                         │
│   }                                                          │
│ }                                                            │
│ </tool_call>                                                 │
